Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Mince @chives{¼%ounce}. Trim and discard woody bottom ends from @asparagus{6%ounce}; cut stalks crosswise into 1-inch pieces.

Place potatoes in a large #pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until very tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid, then drain.

Return potatoes to pot and add @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon}, half the chives, and 1 TBSP @butter{2%tablespoon}. Mash with a #potato masher{}, adding splashes of reserved cooking liquid as needed, until smooth and creamy. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cover to keep warm.

While potatoes cook, toss asparagus on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper. Roast on middle rack until tender and lightly browned, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pat @beef tenderloin filets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with salt and pepper. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add beef and cook to desired doneness, ~{4-7%minutes} per side.

Remove from heat; transfer beef to a #plate{} to rest. Wipe out pan.

Add @beef demi-glace{1%unit}, half the @white balsamic vinegar{5%teaspoon}, and ¼ cup water to pan used for beef over medium-high heat. Bring to a simmer and cook until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from heat and stir in 1 TBSP butter until melted. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide beef, asparagus, and mashed potatoes between plates. Drizzle beef with sauce. Garnish with remaining chives and serve.

> Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.